contentrichtext.text: '''Kirwan''' may refer to: * One of the fourteen [[Tribes of Galway]] * [[Kirwan, Queensland]], suburb in the city of Townsville, Queensland, Australia * [[Château Kirwan]], Bordeaux wine producer, formerly named simply Kirwan * [[Kairouan]], also known as Kirwan, the capital of the Kairouan Governorate in Tunisia ;People * [[A. D. Kirwan]] (1904–1971), former professor, administrator, coach and president of the University of Kentucky * [[Danny Kirwan]], guitarist with Fleetwood Mac from 1968 to 1972 * [[Dervla Kirwan]], actress * [[Eilis Kirwan]], Irish filmmaker * [[James Kirwan]] was a physician to [[Louis XV]] * [[John Kirwan (disambiguation)]], several persons of this name * [[Larry Kirwan]], musician and playwright best known for his work with Black 47 * [[Richard Kirwan]] of Galway, prominent philosopher and chemist * [[Richard Bui Kirwan]] of Cregg Castle, a soldier with Dillon's Regiment at [[Fontenoy]] * [[William E Kirwan]], Chancellor of the University of Maryland System * [[William F Kirwan]], American economist known for his work in sports economics * [[Nicholas Murray]] (1802–1861), Irish-American writer, whose pseudonym was Kirwan {{disambig}}
